codex
The full results revealed the decisive confound, not just a tuning effect: `ReceiverPrior` is applied as a normal GNSS update to a zero-state filter whose covariance is 1, with prior variance also 1. The “truth-equivalent” ECEF position is therefore initialized at half Earth radius, leaving a ~3,189 km radial error that horizontal replay scoring hides; Doppler prediction sees it and converts the geometric residual into velocity. I’m adding the exact-initialization control now to isolate this mechanism from R/Q/geometry/rate effects.
